article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson 84, Robert Morris 79
article.story: CORAOPOLIS, Pa. (AP) -- Senior forward Andre Harris scored 34 points, including the 1,000th of his career, to lead Fairleigh Dickinson to an 84-79 win over Robert Morris on Thursday. Harris shot 12-for-18 from the field and 8-for-11 from the line and raised his career scoring total to 1,001 points. He also had 10 rebounds for Fairleigh Dickinson (11-10, 5-5 Northeast Conference). Manny Ubilla added 18 points, and Sean Baptiste and Michael Peeples each had 10 in the win. Jeremy Chappell scored 23 points, A.J. Jackson 18 and Derek Coleman 13 for Robert Morris (13-7, 5-6), which led 47-46 at halftime.
